HEADWORD: Opinionated
<hw>O*pin"ion*a`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Stiff in
opinion; firmly or unduly adhering to one's own opinion or to
preconceived notions; obstinate in opinion.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

